{
  "texts": [
    "A study conducted by Gao et al.",
    "in collaboration with the University of Chicago demonstrated that blinded human reviewers could correctly identify only 68% of AIgenerated abstracts [12].",
    "If only human reviewers were relied on, this could lead to seepage of AI-generated texts into the hallowed scriptures of scientific literature, which could prove disastrous.Therefore, the integrity of the scientific method must be preserved.",
    "Though machines play an important role, it has to be a human mind that thinks critically and suggests the hypothesis, designs the experiment, and finally, analyses the data [13].",
    "The following ethical and legal issues must be considered before using AI in medical research and healthcare."
  ]
}